==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Madcap
<hw>Mad"cap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Inclined
to wild sports; delighting in rash, absurd, or dangerous
amusements.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The merry <xex>madcap</xex> lord.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Wild; reckless.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Madcap</xex>
follies⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Madcap</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Madcap
<hw>Mad"cap`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person of wild behavior; an
excitable, rash, violent person.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Madden</ent>⟦br⟧
